snippet.textDisplay: When i was younger i never understood being “unable” to watch a movie. When the new Aladdin was coming out, i accidentally clicked a different, community-college made garbage Aladdin that is trying to steal views. It just sucked. There was nothing good about it. The cgi sucked, the plot was completely nonsensical, and the musicals lasted 15 seconds with terrible verses. For instance, “Aladdin” was in the lion cave and had to cross a rope over fire that looked nothing like fire, so he crossed it like a goddamn monkey upside down practically burning alive. When the genie came out and it wasn’t Will Smith i dipped. Ever since then, i’ve developed the self control to not watch terrible movies such as cats, and the other two in this video that i’ve never even heard of.
